"Every year our U.S. government spends millions on funding for the prevention of marijuana users and the entering of marijuana into our country. Many people say that Marijuana kills brain cells but the truth is, that there is no test that says Marijuana really does kill brain cells. In fact, the only thing in Marijuana that kills brain cells is the smoke itself or loss of oxygen while smoking alot of it during one sitting. If we legalize marijuana, not only will our country save money on the prevention of it, our trade with other hemp-legal countries will dramatically increase and prices and inflation will decrease. Taxes will be lowered and marijuana will be the best thing that ever happened to our beautiful country. Even citizens that don't use marijuana will benefit from it! Our constitution doesn't say anything about marijuana and It's not that important to be illegal in our nation. Marijuana is a very mild delicate drug and there is no reason for it to be illegal."
